column5: rest in peace Glenn frey  Had the pleasure of seeing them a few times  http://www.tmz.com/2016/01/18/glenn-frey-the-eagles-dead/
Yeah, just heard thus on the radio. Crazy. RIP.  S.
And for you wrestling fans, "Iron" Mike Sharpe died today as well

I've been an Eagles fan since I was a teenager, but never got to see them until the Hell Freezes Over tour.  I was blown away at how tight they were....and their harmonies were pitch perfect.  The Eagles influenced me big time....both in guitar as well as vocally, and Glenn Frey was a big part of my musical development.  A true music pioneer is gone....RIP Glenn....thanks for everything.
Gary Loizzo: American Breed Singer Dies at 70  Just saw that one too a little while ago.
